-- Cocoa Futures Rebound in New York, Head for Biggest Rally Since April 20
-- Steve Stroth
-- 2010-07-01T13:58:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/cocoa-futures-rebound-in-new-york-head-for-biggest-rally-since-april-20.html

          
          
             Cocoa for September delivery rose
$92, or 3.1 percent, to $3,036 a metric ton at 9:57 a.m. on ICE
Futures U.S. in New York. A close at that price would be the
biggest gain since April 20. Earlier, the price gained as much
as 3.8 percent. Before today, the contract fell 6.2 percent.  
          
          


  


        